ENTRY       EC 4.2.1.144                Enzyme
NAME        3-amino-5-hydroxybenzoate synthase;
            AHBA synthase;
            rifK (gene name)
CLASS       Lyases;
            Carbon-oxygen lyases;
            Hydro-lyases
SYSNAME     5-amino-5-deoxy-3-dehydroshikimate hydro-lyase (3-amino-5-hydroxybenzoate-forming)
REACTION    5-amino-5-deoxy-3-dehydroshikimate = 3-amino-5-hydroxybenzoate + H2O [RN:R06595]
ALL_REAC    R06595
SUBSTRATE   5-amino-5-deoxy-3-dehydroshikimate [CPD:C12108]
PRODUCT     3-amino-5-hydroxybenzoate [CPD:C12107];
            H2O [CPD:C00001]
COMMENT     A pyridoxal 5'-phosphate enzyme. The enzyme from the bacterium Amycolatopsis mediterranei participates in the pathway for rifamycin B biosynthesis. The enzyme also functions as a transaminase earlier in the pathway, producing UDP-alpha-D-kanosamine [3].
